        {
          "feedback": "DNS translates domain names to IP addresses. If a computer has an old IP address cached, it will try to connect to the old server.",
          "isCorrect": true,
          "text": "DNS lookup caching the outdated routing data"
        },
        {
          "feedback": "TCP/TLS establishes the connection, but the issue here is that the browser is trying to connect to the wrong destination entirely.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "TCP/TLS handshakes failing to securely connect"
        },
        {
          "feedback": "HTTP requests happen after a connection is made to an IP address. The failure here happens before the request reaches the new server.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "HTTP request routing misdirecting the data"
